<subSubSection id="2EA1F709BE71AA63CB29B2DEF29502FA" pageId="0" pageNumber="4421" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="4587F86C9194B53D4766982F5959ADA1" pageId="0" pageNumber="4421">Distribution</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D4B109BBBD0240FA6ED50115713FF021" pageId="0" pageNumber="4421">
Known distribution: Antilles, Colombia, Costa Rica, Ecuador, El Salvador, Guatemala, Honduras, Mexico, Nicaragua, Panama, United States of America and Venezuela (
<bibRefCitation id="A78FF6D3993D6B707094E0FB1D14C8A8" author="Moran, R. C." editor="Davidse, G." journalOrPublisher="Universidad Nacional Autonoma de Mexico, Ciudad de Mexico" pageId="0" pageNumber="4421" title="Flora Mesoamericana" year="1995">Moran 1995b</bibRefCitation>
). Fig. 19.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="06B06DBC17F5E502D0424C7C198D9C78" pageId="0" pageNumber="4421" type="ecology">
<paragraph id="E81B74D62B61D6965727E675280C6852" pageId="0" pageNumber="4421">Ecology</paragraph>
<paragraph id="307F1002F7AE71C0DCAAE67FB1F42DA0" pageId="0" pageNumber="4421">Occurs as terrestrial or rupestrial in montane wet and seasonal forests.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="E23CB9BD7B7E20206323FDE531983148" pageId="0" pageNumber="4421" type="taxon discussion">
<paragraph id="573895279C8286F345FEA00BEDBCE13D" pageId="0" pageNumber="4421">Taxon discussion</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E28F7E09C51FD3DB7630734AD4A675BB" pageId="0" pageNumber="4421">
This is a very common species in Central America, also occurring in northern South America. It can be recognized by peltate indusia and entire pinnae or lobes (
<bibRefCitation id="770F5BCB803207DA0206EF3E83C5A33F" author="Moran, R. C." editor="Davidse, G." journalOrPublisher="Universidad Nacional Autonoma de Mexico, Ciudad de Mexico" pageId="0" pageNumber="4421" title="Flora Mesoamericana" year="1995">Moran 1995b</bibRefCitation>
). The closest species is 
<taxonomicName id="2F925C5ABFDB357D653D6D88C8F1F22D" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Tectariaceae" genus="Tectaria" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Tectaria incisa" order="Polypodiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="4421" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="incisa">Tectaria incisa</taxonomicName>
Cav., from which 
<taxonomicName id="CC69C3D13624C08C2A1B8DE1F741EA6D" authority="" authorityName="" class="Centricae" family="Chironomidae" genus="T." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="T. heracleifolia" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="4421" phylum="Diatomeae" rank="species" species="heracleifolia">T. heracleifolia</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished by peltate indusia, cordiform bases of pinnae and apical segment and smaller number of pinnae (
<bibRefCitation id="4374CCB4567C49B53217B4D82882B7E9" author="Moran, R. C." editor="Davidse, G." journalOrPublisher="Universidad Nacional Autonoma de Mexico, Ciudad de Mexico" pageId="0" pageNumber="4421" title="Flora Mesoamericana" year="1995">Moran 1995b</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
